The group needs to post weekly (by Fridays 16:00) a status update (weekly progress report) to their Moodle discussion area. See lecture 1 slides for first deadline date. In the progress report, you must describe the current status of your project with regard to the original plan and schedule. During the independent work week you do not need to post a progress report in Moodle, but of course you may do so if you wish.

In the first progress report, provide the functionality diagrams and the schedule (plan it weekly per task), and a work allocation plan among group members (who will do what). This is your project plan. Please format the reports properly into PDFs before posting them on the group discussion area. You can work on the report together, or assign the preparation responsibility to some group members in any way your group sees fit. The report is considered to be submitted by the group, not by the individual posting it in Moodle.


